locality: Mazombe Division, Image Ward, Image Mountains Forest Reserve, Irawu village, Idunduge valley going west at Iyai water pipe intake.

About 11 km NW of Singida. Slightly undulating plains, here very slight valley with black clay. Sparse shrubland (Acacia drepanolobium Terminalia) with damp grass (Sporobolus) & large patches of low Rhynchosia.
Between Bathurst and Port Alfred, at 46 km marker. Close to St. Francis Health Centre/Kleinemonde turn-off

Ngorongoro Conservation Area, Ndiyan, 4 km North of Endulen Village. In savanna dominated by grass. Refered as heighland, osopuko by the Maasai. Information given by Ole Nakuroi, ca. 85 years and Lepilal Ole Nakuroi, warrior, ca. 30 year.
